<!-- Debian Network Administartor's Manual - Mail -->

  <chapt id="mail">
  <heading>Mail</heading>
<p>
author: not yet determined
<p>
This section describes how to setup different mail handling servers
(daemons) on Debian. Here you will find information on Internet mail
and pointers for you on how to handle it. Of course, not every detail
will be described here - only the Debian specific differences.

<p>
  <sect>Post Office Protocol (POP3) software
    <sect1>qpopper
    </sect1>
    <sect1>ipop3d
    </sect1>
  </sect>

  <sect>Interactive Mail Access Protocol (IMAP) software
    <sect1>imapd
    </sect1>
  </sect>

  <sect>Simple Mail Transfer Protocol (SMTP) software
    <sect1>sendmail
    </sect1>
    <sect1>smail
    </sect1>
    <sect1>exim
    </sect1>
    <sect1>postfix
    </sect1>
    <sect1>zmailer
    </sect1>
    <sect1>ssmtp
    </sect1>
  </sect>

